to begin the Gui install first type and enter "archinstall"
wait for the gui to open
now working from the top, use arrow keys to navigate and enter to open them
select your language(normally set to your region install for me the default is english so i can leave it alone)

locales can also be left alone unless you know your keyboard uses

in mirrors and repositories, press select region and pick your region
once selected you can press back 

in disk configuration, partitioning, use best-effort
select what drive(or unallocated space you dual boot) you want to install linux 
btrfs, yes, Use Compression

in LVM, default, btrfs, yes, Use Compression

you can skip Disk encryption, if you would like to use it follow these steps (only useful on devices that might be stolen:laptops, it isnt useful on desktops) 
encryption type, LVM on LUKS
add a password for the encrytion
skip iteration time
in partitions select what you want encrypted
press back

in btrfs snapshots, TimeShift
press back

skip swap

in bootloader, bootloader, Grub
press back

skip kernal

Change hostname if you would like (name of the device)

in authentication, root password, enter a password for your root
in user account, add a user, enter your name/username, enter your password, make your main account sudo(press yes), add any extra accounts you would like when finished press confirm and exit
press back

in profile, type, Desktop, hyprland, seatd
in greeter, ly
press back 

in applications, blutooth, yes, audio, pipewire, power management, power-profile-deamon
press back

in network configuration, copy iso

in additional packages add the following:
(install all if you dont know what your doing, if you do feel free to skip or add a few more)
(use /"package name" to search for them)

amd-ucode - updates for amd cpu 
base - required
base-devel - dev packages
blueman - bluetooth applet
btrfs-progs - file system management needed for btrfs  
cmake - needed to build certain files
discord - names says it all
efibootmgr - required by grub 
flatpak - needed to install packages using flat hub
git - installs git 
gnome-disk-utility
grim - screenshot tool
grub - bootloader
grub-btrfs - adds btrfs support to grub
impression - used to make bootinstallers in linux
inotify-tools - needed for grub btrfs deamon to spot new snapshots
kitty - personal fav terminal
kitty-shell-intergration
kitty-terminfo
linux - required
linux-firmware - required
ly - login manager
nautilus - file explorer 
neovim - personal fav IDE
networkmanager - easy network management 
obsidian - note taking app
openrgb - for led control
openssh - to utilize ssh 
pipewire - needed For audio
pipewire-alsa - needed for audio framework
pipewire-pulse - needed for audio framework
pipewire-jack - needed for audio framework
prismlauncher - minecraft java launcher
reflector - manage mirrors for pacman
sudo - to run commands as other users
timeshift - a gui to utilize snapshots  
ttf-bigblueterminal-nerd
vlc - media player
waybar - taskbar for hypr
wireplumber - pipewire session manager
wofi - application search for hypr 

in timezone, "select your timezone"

now press install, yes
(if it fails turn off pc remove usb turn pc on, turn pc off put usb back in and attempt the install again)

wait for the installations to complete
once complete press reboot system, remove usb once screen goes black\

once logged in press super(windows button) + q 

type the following commands:
(type y and press enter whenever promted)
sudo pacman -S network-manager-applet
flatpak remote-add --if-not-exists flathub https://dl.flathub.org/repo/flathub.flatpakrepo
flatpak install flathub org.vinegarhq.Sober com.bambulab.BambuStudio com.valvesoftware.Steam app.zen_browser.zen
git clone https://github.com/LazyVim/starter ~/.config/nvim
rm -rf ~/.config/nvim/.git
nvim

once everything is installed and nvim is open
press super + c to close everything 

press super + q and type nautilus
press the arrow in the bottom right and show hidden files, .config, hypr

